  "prompt": "Is my maternal cousin's maternal cousin, my cousin?",
  "response": "To determine the relationship, let's break it down step-by-step.\n\n1. **Your Maternal Cousin**: This is someone who shares the same maternal grandparents with you. Let's call this person Cousin A.\n\n2. **Cousin A's Maternal Cousin**: This is someone who shares the same maternal grandparents with Cousin A. Let's call this person Cousin B.\n\nNow, we need to figure out how Cousin B is related to you.\n\n- Since Cousin A is your maternal cousin, Cousin A's maternal grandparents are your maternal grandparents.\n- Cousin B, being Cousin A's maternal cousin, also shares the same maternal grandparents as Cousin A.\n\nTherefore, Cousin B shares the same maternal grandparents as you, which means Cousin B is also your maternal cousin.\n\nSo, yes, your maternal cousin's maternal cousin is also your cousin, specifically your maternal cousin.",
